    # [Scene: Municipal Offices — Council Chamber | Morning]

    scene bg ch15_771f04_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fast, bright strings under percussion; a marching rhythm layered with choral breaths]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Murmurs rise and fall like tide; camera shutters; a distant gull cries]
    "You taste salt and coffee; both are sharp and ordinary. The room is a contained storm—heat from bodies, the high sheen of cameras, the low hum of generators outside. Dr. Noor's chart is on the lectern,"
    "a knot of ink and benchmarks you've spent sleepless nights translating into something the public can trust. The decision you coaxed into being—binding authority with phased pilot benchmarks and community oversight—hangs between everyone like newly laced"
    "rope."
    "Your palms are warm against the pages of the draft. Legal clauses, rollback protections for Flooded Row, escrow language tying funding releases to transparent audits: words you chose to hold people, not just numbers."
    show dr_noor_patel at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_noor_patel "If we phrase the trigger points here—pilot survival at year one, community audit every six months, and an independent ombudsperson—this isn't just a promise. It's enforceable caregiving."
    show ari_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "It has to be measurable. If we make metrics vague, money moves and lives don't. If we make them impossible, no one signs. We need thresholds people can see with their own eyes."
    show sora_watanabe at center:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "And we need people in those rooms. Not just faces for cameras—actual seats, rotating, with real oversight and recall powers."
    "A dozen hands in the crowd clap; it's not the falling kind—it's the staccato, urgent clapping of people who've spent months climbing the same incline."
    hide dr_noor_patel
    show lina_moreau at left:
        zoom 0.7

    lina_moreau "Binding authority sounds heavy. But we framed it as conditional and phased. It grows only when the pilots show success and the community signs off. Public funds move with public accountability. That is governance, not gift."
    "You watch her mouth the last line as if to remind herself. Her hand brushes the tablet at her hip; she doesn't reach for it. The gesture is small. Your chest, which had been tight, loosens a fraction."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A sudden cheer from the back; someone starts a chant that folds into the room—"People decide! People decide!"]
    "Maya slips into the space beside you, cheeks smeared with mud from the wetland brigades, hair tucked under her fisher's hat. Her grin is wide and immediate, the kind that cracks a weathered face open to something younger. She taps the stack of pledge sheets."
    hide ari_navarro
    show maya_cruz at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_cruz "We got enough signatures this week to prove the pilots had public buy-in. We even tracked the donors—no opaque shells. People stayed up to translate the legal language into plain words. That helped."
    hide sora_watanabe
    show ari_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "You always do the translation work no one sees."

    maya_cruz "Someone's got to plant the reeds and read the fine print."

    menu:
        "Clasp Lina's hand briefly before you go on stage":
            "You fold your fingers around Lina's thumb for a second—firm, quick. It's not a flourish; it's a contract between two people in the middle of a public act. Lina's mouth softens. She squeezes back, a tiny private agreement in the bright room."
        "Adjust Sora's bandana knot when they pass you the mic":
            "You reach out and tighten Sora's bandana without thinking. Their grin widens; the gesture is practical and intimate both. They bump your shoulder with a familiar, conspiratorial jolt. The crowd doesn't notice the smallness, but you do."

    # --- merge ---
    "The scene continues with the main narrative as written."
    hide lina_moreau
    hide maya_cruz
    hide ari_navarro

    scene bg ch15_771f04_2 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Brass swells; a sharp drum roll]
    "You step up to the lectern because you promised a plan that would hold people. The microphones angle toward your mouth like open rivers. Your voice carries—clear, practiced, human."
    show ari_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "We are not here for headlines. We're here because people woke up in the dark and chose to make morning tools. This council—our hybrid model—will link public funding to demonstrable pilot success, transparent audits, and enforceable rollback protections for neighborhoods at the highest risk. It ties engineers and activists to the same ledger: accountability."
    show sora_watanabe at right:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "This isn't the end of the argument. It's the equipment for the argument. It keeps us honest."

    "Volunteer" "If this council can stop that developer from moving in without community oversight—if it keeps people from being forced out—I'll sign anything."
    show lina_moreau at center:
        zoom 0.7

    lina_moreau "We wrote in specific clauses to block unilateral sale or reclassification of at-risk parcels. We built in recall triggers if the oversight fails. This is—as much as policy can be—a promise we can enforce."
    "You and Lina begin a back-and-forth that the room leans into. The lines blend policy and care, legal jargon and lived memory. It's a conversation that refuses to be polite—because politeness would be betrayal. It is"
    "instead precise and affectionate in the way of people who love a place enough to argue with its bones."

    lina_moreau "If we allow a staggered escrow, funders release funds yearly instead of all at once—"

    ari_navarro "—and every release requires an independent audit plus a community assembly confirmation. No back channels. No early releases without documented benchmarks."

    sora_watanabe "And the advisory seats rotate. No seat held by the same person for more than two years unless reaffirmed by citizens' vote."
    hide ari_navarro
    show dr_noor_patel at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_noor_patel "We can operationalize the benchmarks—survival of living shoreline segments, biodiversity metrics, and social outcomes like displacement numbers. Data that shows we're not just moving sand—we're moving lives forward."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A judge's gavel translated into the rhythm of many hands, clapping; the room sounds like a sea of small decisions aligning into a single current]
    "You sign the cover sheet first—your pen feels slick and real. Lina signs next, a clean line. Sora steps up and signs with a slightly theatrical flourish that earns a laugh and makes the camera lenses"
    "bloom. Maya kneels at the table and fits her signature into the margin like planting a reed."
    "Community Member after community member steps forward. The pledges are for oversight, transparency, pilots, rollback protections. The list grows; it becomes a living thing with the heft of real signatures and the texture of a town's labor."
    # [Scene: Reclaimed Wetland Garden | Late Morning]
    hide sora_watanabe
    hide lina_moreau
    hide dr_noor_patel

    scene bg ch15_771f04_3 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: High-tempo percussion with handclaps and whistles; a communal rhythm]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Children laughing; the slap of oars on floats; reeds whispering]
    "The garden smells of peat and salt and sweat. People fold tents, exchange thermoses, band members tune guitars on the far side. It's noisy in the best way: productive, messy, alive."
    "You walk the boardwalk watching hands—callused, delicate, instinctive—finish the last of the planting. Each plant is a small argument against erasure. Each one is a tiny, stubborn 'we remain.'"
    "Sora Watanabe finds you and loops an arm through the crook of your elbow, an easy, unceremonious closeness. The bandana flutters like a banner."
    show sora_watanabe at left:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "They told me I was being naive. Then they showed up with shovels."
    show ari_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "You showed them how to make the case. You made anger practical."

    sora_watanabe "And you made the plan that looks like it can be governed. That's why they signed."
    "The two of you share a grin that says: this is work; it's the most romantic thing we've ever done."
    "Maya hustles over, cheeks flushed, hands still damp with mud."
    show maya_cruz at center:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_cruz "Brigades reported improved sediment capture in the southern marsh plot. The pilot plots are actually holding. I swear, when we cleared debris last month, I thought everything was gone—but it came back."
    "You press your thumb into a wet clump of soil; it gives, then stays. It's a small, honest proof."

    menu:
        "Offer to write the first community report with Dr. Noor":
            "You suggest pairing data with testimony. Dr. Noor nods, already sketching out a framework. The work feels—right. It's rigorous and human."
        "Join Maya's brigade for an afternoon instead of staying on paperwork":
            "You kick off your boots and get your hands in the mud, lifting a clump of roots with Maya. She teases you about being 'too neat' and you laugh, and the day feels like something repaired where nothing dramatic happened—only steady, mutual tending."

