    # [Scene: Tidewatch Institute — Rooftop Greenhouse | Afternoon]
    hide sora_watanabe
    hide ari_navarro
    hide maya_cruz

    scene bg ch15_771f04_4 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Optimistic synth pads; layered with the steady pulse of conversation]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The hiss of irrigation, keyboard clicks, soft laughter]
    "Dr. Noor and a cluster of young researchers walk you through the pilot results: side-by-side photos showing marsh growth, sensor readouts tracking erosion rates, community surveys that quantify perceived safety and cultural preservation. The numbers are not miraculous; they're real—gradual but decisive."
    show dr_noor_patel at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_noor_patel "At six months, Pilot A has reduced nearshore erosion by nineteen percent versus the control. Biodiversity indices show a significant uptick. Social surveys report lower displacement anxiety in households adjacent to the pilot zones."
    show ari_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "Nineteen percent is more than a statistic. It's a handful of houses that stayed put. It's a kitchen window that didn't get swallowed by the sea."
    show lina_moreau at center:
        zoom 0.7

    lina_moreau "We will present these to the regional board with a strict funding-release schedule tied to these metrics. No ambiguity."
    hide dr_noor_patel
    show sora_watanabe at left:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "Make sure the presentation includes the lived stories. Data alone won't carry the emotional truth to a boardroom."

    ari_navarro "We do both. Numbers and names. Policy and memory."
    "The greenhouse feels like a small sanctum of possibility; growth under glass. Your watch beeps with a barometric tick—an old habit. You look up at Lina; the amber light catches her profile. There is an ease now that didn't exist before: shared fatigue, shared resolve."

    lina_moreau "We argued hard. I learned how to push without flattening the town."

    ari_navarro "And I learned how to hold skepticism without becoming stalled."

    lina_moreau "We're both better for that."
    "You want to say more—a confession of trust, an acknowledgement of debt—but the room is so full of other needs. Instead, you take a breath and let the work speak. Trust becomes procedural; it shows up as public audits, rotating seats, and benchmarks."
    # [Scene: Boardwalk — Evening]
    hide ari_navarro
    hide lina_moreau
    hide sora_watanabe

    scene bg ch15_771f04_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Driving drums, layered with harmonized voices; a celebratory, urgent tempo]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Hammering on a repair bench; distant singing; waves sighing rhythmically]
    "The town has gathered—folk from Flooded Row, youth with paint-splattered faces, elders leaning on canes. There's a liturgy to repair: nets are mended in a circle, planks are replaced, someone patches a child's rubber boot. You move through the crowd with Lina and Sora at your side."
    "Maya leads a group teaching knotwork to volunteers. She demonstrates, and the circle winds tighter as fingers, new and practiced, copy her. A child tugs at your sleeve and asks if you can tie a bow."
    "You do; the child's delighted squeal is a small bell in the thick evening air."
    show sora_watanabe at left:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "Remember when we thought we needed to light the town on fire to get attention? This is louder."
    show ari_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "It is. Quiet work can be loud when enough people do it together."

    "Community Member" "We held them to the terms. They had to pass audits. They had to come before us."

    ari_navarro "And if they don't—"
    show lina_moreau at center:
        zoom 0.7

    lina_moreau "We have legal levers. We built escalation pathways. Accountability is a muscle."
    "There is a filing of paperwork at the municipal office earlier today that you know will blunt a few predatory moves from private developers. It's not absolute, but it's a hedge, and those hedges are what let people sleep with a thinner edge of fear."
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Climactic swell; a communal cheer rises like surf breaking over a reef]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Firecrackers echoing faintly in the distance; a victory chant begins and grows—practical, not triumphalist]
    "The arousal reaches a peak: the speed of activity, the amount of skin in the game, everything accelerating toward a single, sustained effort. The pilot's first milestone has been reached—the point at which escrow releases the next tranche of funding. Volunteers cheer; some cry."
    "You stand between Lina and Sora, both close in different ways. Lina's arm brushes yours; she speaks quietly but with a steady intensity."

    lina_moreau "We didn't do this by stepping on each other's throats. We designed a way for friction to mean progress."

    sora_watanabe "And we channeled the burn into something that binds instead of breaks."

    ari_navarro "We kept people in the room and made the rules visible."
    hide sora_watanabe
    show maya_cruz at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_cruz "And we cleaned the mud out of the drains so kids could play again."
    "The chorus is at its loudest, but beneath it is a sustained, steady beating: long-term work. There is no finale trumpeted with fireworks and finality. There is a continued cadence—a rhythm you are learning to keep."
    hide ari_navarro
    hide lina_moreau
    hide maya_cruz

    scene bg ch15_771f04_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A warm, resolving chord sequence that still carries momentum]
    "You consider the horizon; it is no longer a line of terror but a line of work. There will be more storms, more filings, more nights patching nets and arguing with donors. But now there are"
    "procedures and people who can hold them accountable. That reality is not small; it's the architecture of hope."
    "Sora Watanabe looks at you, then at Lina Moreau, then back at you. Their gaze is an honest map of intention—no rush, just the slow folding of trust into daily practice."
    show sora_watanabe at left:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "There's a lot left to do. Stay with it?"
    show ari_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "I will. I promised to make a plan that saved people, not stats. This—this is the plan in motion."
    show lina_moreau at center:
        zoom 0.7

    lina_moreau "Then we'll keep designing, measuring, and making room for everyone to speak. Together."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The crowd begins a quiet, sustained chant that is less slogan and more an undertaking: "We govern. We care. We stay."]
    "You breathe in, the air tasting of salt, smoke, and hot soup. You let your shoulders drop for the first time in a long while. The arousal decrescendos slightly—not a collapse but a settling—because the highest tension has been poured into the work and is now being transmuted into habit."
    hide sora_watanabe
    hide ari_navarro
    hide lina_moreau

    scene bg ch15_771f04_7 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A final, bright chord lingers; it's not a full resolution, but it promises durability]
    "You close your Moleskine and slide it into your jacket. There are new pages to fill—audits to read, petitions to file, training sessions to run—but for this night, the town carries itself forward. The romance of"
    "governance—slow, stubborn, affectionate—has set a rhythm in your life that is more sustaining than any sudden blaze."
    "You look at the horizon, at the line between sea and sky. It feels like something to work toward rather than run from."
    # [Scene: Municipal Offices — Quiet Hallway | Night]

    scene bg ch15_771f04_8 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Muffled celebration from the chamber; the drip of a leaking gutter]
    "Lina Moreau and Sora Watanabe stand with you in the hallway, an odd, intimate triangle formed by fatigue and purpose. Conversation has slowed into the easy, tough honesty of people who've shared labor. The three of"
    "you talk in turns—plans for the pilot, a list of community liaisons, who will hold which seat on the council rotation."
    show lina_moreau at left:
        zoom 0.7

    lina_moreau "I'll handle the funders' board next week. Keep them on the schedule we agreed."
    show sora_watanabe at right:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "I'll convene the co-ops and the youth brigade. Make sure the rotation is accessible, not just in theory."
    show ari_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "I'll draft the reporting templates and coordinate with Dr. Noor on the independent audits."
    "The exchange is practical, but each sentence carries warmth. Each commitment is a stitch in the same repair job."

    lina_moreau "And when things get ugly politically, I want you both in the room. We can be better negotiators together."

    sora_watanabe "Hell yes. We can make them underestimate a town that knows its own worth."

    ari_navarro "We'll keep one another honest."

    lina_moreau "That's a fair trade."
    "You feel the day's arousal settle into a bright steadiness. There is more strain ahead—litigation, assaults from private interests, inevitable setbacks—but the scaffolding is in place. You feel gratitude, fierce and clean, for the people who"
    "showed up and for the structures you all put in place to ensure the town's voice will continue to be heard."
    hide lina_moreau
    hide sora_watanabe
    hide ari_navarro

    scene bg ch15_771f04_9 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Soft piano overlaying a sustained string resonance—hopeful, earned]
    "You step out into the night air; salt-laced wind meets your face. The town hums behind you—boards being secured, lights being checked, the low lullaby of an ocean that will always demand attention. You inhale and"
    "the work in front of you looks less like a cliff and more like a path built plank by plank."
    "There is closure—not an end, but the completion of a long, necessary arc: you kept your promise to make a plan that holds people. The model you helped design ties money to oversight, success to community"
    "voice, and future funding to living proof. It will be messy, political, fragile; but it will also be legitimate and as resilient as people are when they share responsibility."

    scene bg ch15_771f04_10 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A final, ringing chord that carries both the weight of what was lost and the quiet joy of what has been made]
    "You tuck your Moleskine away, fingers stained with ink and mud and something like renewal. The romance that grew here wasn't sudden or cinematic; it was built in afternoons of policy debates, in mud on the"
    "knees, in tightened bandanas, in signatures, and in the willingness to keep speaking truth to power together."
    "You look at Lina and Sora—two different kinds of steady—and feel the long, slow stitch of trust. It is not a neat bow; it is a durable line tied in a way that will hold."

    scene bg ch15_771f04_11 at full_bg
    "THE END"
